editorialNotes.standard: A rare kind of triumph, Prune takes a simple ideaâpruning treesâand shapes it into a creative, deeply playable puzzle game. The visuals echo the style of Japanese painting in striking fashion, and the beautiful music instills a contemplative tone as you swipe to trim the limbs of a rapidly growing tree and guide it around obstacles. editorialNotes.standard: At a glance, hocus doesnât look very complicated. You swipe to move a red cube along a latticework of plain grey beams.
